Obstacle_Desc: no curb cut for ADA Accessibility on this side of the stop direction

Additional_Comments: Very dangerous to cross from west to east across Glen Iris here. I nearly get hit every single day in the afternoons. Cars headed southbound sometimes pay attention although they’ll blow by me, however those headed northbound crest over a hill and then accelerate downhill with little to no regard to my life or those I ride with. I am a confident urbanist, healthy, and 30. I fear for any child who has interest in crossing this street. Children do cross this street headed to the pond, playground, BeltLine, and now the grocery store. We need to make it safer, preferably with a stop sign.
